---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Diaspora Founder Guides: Honest Intelligence for Ghanaians Abroad"
  description="Practical guides for diaspora Ghanaians considering business or investment in Ghana. GIPC registration, fraud prevention, remote-viable models, and trust mechanisms. No hype."
  keywords="Ghana diaspora investment, diaspora business Ghana, GIPC registration guide, Ghana fraud prevention, remote business Ghana, diaspora founder Ghana"
>
  <div class="hero hero--bg hero--diaspora">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <div class="hero-label">For Ghanaians Abroad</div>
      <h1>Diaspora Founder Guides</h1>
      <p>Practical intelligence for real decisions. What works, what fails, and what will cost you your savings if you skip the due diligence.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="section reveal">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-label">Published</div>
        <div class="section-title">Guides</div>
      </div>

      <div class="card-grid">
        <a href="/diaspora/remote-viable-businesses" class="article-card">
          <span class="card-tag guide">Diaspora Guide</span>
          <h3>Remote-Viable Businesses: What Actually Works</h3>
          <p>After 40+ analytical cycles, we found no general-founder model that is genuinely remote-viable from Day 1. Here is what that means and the two conditional exceptions.</p>
          <div class="card-meta"><span>March 29, 2026</span><span>Business Models</span><span>14 min read</span></div>
        </a>

        <a href="/diaspora/gipc-registration-guide" class="article-card">
          <span class="card-tag guide">Diaspora Guide</span>
          <h3>GIPC Registration Guide 2026</h3>
          <p>Step-by-step registration process, costs in dual currency, realistic timelines, and the $200,000 minimum capital reform that could change everything.</p>
          <div class="card-meta"><span>March 29, 2026</span><span>Regulation</span><span>12 min read</span></div>
        </a>

        <a href="/diaspora/trust-and-fraud-prevention" class="article-card">
          <span class="card-tag risk">Diaspora Guide</span>
          <h3>Trust and Fraud Prevention for Diaspora Investors</h3>
          <p>The specific fraud types that hit diaspora businesses in Ghana. Cash theft, ghost workers, supplier collusion, land disputes, and the control systems that prevent them.</p>
          <div class="card-meta"><span>March 29, 2026</span><span>Risk Management</span><span>14 min read</span></div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
